Dear Annamalai,

I have reviewed the v3 document in full. This is the most significant 
single-version improvement in the entire SPINRISE project. Let me be 
specific about what is excellent before addressing what still needs to 
be done.

*What v3 has achieved*

Stage 0 is now confirmed with numbers. The form was cleaned from 
approximately 8,200 lines to 7,400 lines. Zero CustID blocks. TL-Dev 
Sasi's sign-off is recorded. This closes the most critical structural 
question that has been open since v1. The What Changed v2-to-v3 table 
documents all seven improvements explicitly — *this is exactly the 
traceability standard the project requires.
*
The SP analysis is the strongest improvement. All three stored 
procedures are now documented from actual SQL code — 
KSP_LSALES_SALEORDER with all CASE and IF branches, 
KSP_TCSAmountCheckLSales with the full UNION ALL logic across six 
invoice tables, and Ksp_PendingOrderVal with complete join semantics. 
*This is the RMI PO standard and you have met it.*

The audit trail is restored in Section 8.3 as Step 8 of the Save 
Sequence with the complete ig_trans_log_sales field mapping. The 
regression from v1 is corrected. Six Critical Defects are formally 
raised in Section 12 with specific SPINRISE fixes — the race condition, 
the missing transaction wrapper, SQL injection, the temp table PK gap, 
the Crystal credentials, and the delivery schedule race. The Section 11 
Customer Variation Register now has four columns including SPINRISE 
config names and defaults. Forty-two error messages documented. The 
auto-email flow is fully documented. *All nine areas of the scorecard 
have improved from v2 to v3.*

*Annamalai, this is a professionally prepared FSD document. The 
technical work is acknowledged.
*
*Three corrections you must make — by Monday 13 April morning session*

These are developer-side corrections that do not require IST input.

*First:* CSM fields must be marked as Phase 2. The CEO decision on CSM 
was made during the IST review cycle on 11 April — CSM integration is 
not live at any customer site, was stopped due to system corruption, and 
will be designed fresh in Phase 2. The Phase 1 SPINRISE sale order form 
must not implement the CSM checkbox, CSM Work Order No., CSM Sale Order 
No., or the REST API call. In Sections 2.2, 3, and 5, mark all 
CSM-related fields and logic as Phase 2 features excluded from Phase 1 
scope. *In Section 12, add a note: CSM integration deferred to Phase 2 — 
not in scope for Phase 1 development.
*
*Second: *TCS threshold hard-coded in SP must be added as a Critical 
Defect. Seenivasan confirmed in the IST review that the TCS threshold is 
handled within KSP_TCSAmountCheckLSales SP logic and is not separately 
configurable in any table. The CEO directed this to be added to Section 
12 as a Critical Defect. It is not there. Please add it: CD-7 — TCS 
threshold hard-coded in KSP_TCSAmountCheckLSales SP. Not configurable. 
*SPINRISE fix: move threshold to a dedicated TCS configuration table 
read as a parameter by the SP.*

*Third:* Section 5.6 Document Number Generation needs a warning callout. 
CD-1 correctly identifies the race condition in Section 12. But Section 
5.6 describes the IG_DOCCONTROL generation mechanism without flagging 
that the current implementation lacks UPDLOCK. *Add a single warning 
line: 'CRITICAL DEFECT CD-1: This MAX+1 read is performed WITHOUT 
UPDLOCK. See Section 12.1 for fix.'
*
*On Section 13 IST answers — what I am seeing
*
*Annamalai, I need to be direct about something important. *Seven of the 
thirteen IST questions in Section 13 have answers that read as 'Default 
values N' or 'Default values 0' or 'Default values 100'. These are not 
IST answers. These are the default values from Section 11 that you have 
already correctly documented. IST-1 asks which live customers have 
non-standard ig_param settings — that answer is not 'Default values N.' 
IST-2 asks who sets App_Flg after a sale order is saved — that answer is 
not 'Default values N.' IST-4 asks which live customers have 
CRLimitLockFlg='Y' — Seenivasan already told us in the IST mail exchange 
that only Bannari uses it. Why is that not recorded here?

*Section 13 can only be completed by Seenivasan from his field 
experience at customer sites.* You cannot complete it from the code. The 
defaults belong in Section 11 — which you have correctly done. The IST 
answers belong in Section 13 — which only Seenivasan can provide.

I understand you may have added these default values to make the 
document appear complete before submission. *Do not do this. *An FSD 
with fabricated IST answers is worse than one with blank IST fields, 
because it obscures what is actually missing. *Leave the IST fields 
blank or mark them '[Seenivasan — IST answer required]' and submit to 
Seenivasan immediately.
*
*For Seenivasan — IST-1 to IST-13 answers due Monday 13 April AN.*

Seenivasan, the v3 FSD is technically ready for IST review. The 
developer has done his part and done it well. Your IST review of Section 
13 is the gating step. You need to answer all 13 IST questions from your 
own field experience. Several of these you have already answered in the 
mail exchange — do not repeat the work, simply transfer those answers 
into Section 13 directly.

IST-4: You already confirmed only Bannari uses CRLimitLockFlg='Y'. 
Record this.
IST-7: You already confirmed IG_PARAM.Despatch_Instruction controls the 
IG_INSBODT vs IG_BODT routing. Record this.
IST-9: You confirmed CSM is not live — but a customer used it and plans 
to reuse. Record which customer.
IST-10: You confirmed automail is not used by any customer currently. 
Record this.
IST-8: You confirmed TCS threshold is hard-coded in the SP. Record this.

For the questions where you have not yet provided answers in the mail 
thread — IST-1 (non-standard ig_param settings at live sites), IST-2 
(App_Flg approval screen name and user role), IST-3 (pending order value 
includes only approved orders — is this correct?), IST-5 (minimum 5 
support call patterns), IST-6 (JW only or other contract types), IST-11 
(RepLSales.rpt — multiple versions across sites?), IST-12 (what is 
handled manually at year-end?) —*these are the fresh answers needed.*

*Also: the two follow-ups from the earlier CEO mail that remain open.* 
CRLimitLockFlg='N' path — when the Yes/No warning appears, can any 
logged-in user override or is there a user-level check? And the Scrap 
Sales contract type code — what is the exact code in ig_conttype that 
represents Scrap Sales, since TCS applies only to that contract type?

*Deadline for Seenivasan:* complete and send your Section 13 IST answers 
to Annamalai by *Monday 13 April, 4:00 PM.*

*For TL-IST Palanivel — TL-IST sign-off deadline Monday 13 April 6.00PM.
*
Once Seenivasan sends his IST answers and Annamalai incorporates them, 
the document goes to you for TL-IST independent review. Your review must 
follow the checklist standard — agree or correct each IST answer from 
your own senior IST experience, do not simply forward. Given the short 
week, your TL-IST sign-off deadline is Monday 13 April by 6.00PM , so PM 
Saravanan can do his Stage 4 review on Monday by EoD and the FSD 
*reaches CEO for approval by Monday 8.30PM
*
I am aware this is a tight schedule. SPINRISE is the priority task. 
Operational customer issues must be managed alongside SPINRISE work, not 
instead of it.

*For TL-Dev Sasi*

Stage 0 sign-off on M03 is confirmed and recorded. Thank you. One item: 
the v3 document refers to TDS_GrossAmt in Section 11 as a configurable 
parameter but the SP analysis in Section 8 shows the threshold is 
hard-coded in the SP code. Please confirm for Annamalai: is TDS_GrossAmt 
actually read by the SP from a table, or is it a constant inside the SP 
body? This determines whether CD-7 is 'fix the SP to read from table' or 
'create new table and wire it up.'

*Summary of deadlines*

Annamalai — three corrections (CSM Phase 2 marking, TCS CD-7, Section 
5.6 warning): Monday 13 April, morning session.
Seenivasan — IST-1 to IST-13 complete answers sent to Annamalai: Monday 
13 April, 4:00 PM.
Annamalai — v3 updated with IST answers and submitted to Palanivel: 
Monday 13 April, 5.00PM.
Palanivel — TL-IST review and sign-off: Monday 13 April, 6.00PM.
PM Saravanan — Stage 4 review and sign-off: Monday 8.30PM
*CEO approval target:Tuesday 14 April.*

Regards,
T. Mani
